<br>
   Out of nowhere Ordit says he rolled to helpbot and that the number was 5, and that his friend Flizor had won the disk.  They both then left the party and left the mission.<br>
<br>
   I called an ARK on the situation, think that if I explained the situation, that being that their be honesty upheld in AO, that we'd get the disk back.  Well, guess what, your ARK's said they couldn't do anything due to the fact they were in team and that they are allowed to loot whatever, and that the agreement we made prior to the mission has no substance whatsoever in this situation.<br>
<br>
   Personally this makes me sick.  Your loophole rules promote thievery and dishonesty, which makes people like me, who's account is comming up to be renewed in a few days, not even want to renew.  Anarchy Online has become a haven for thieves and little punk kids who can rob other players of their hard earned items and leaves us who try to play the game with honesty and dignity, with our hands tied, and our pockets empty.  You should really consider revamping your rules concerning this before you lose more customers than just myself.<br>
<br>
If FunCom supports dishonesty and unfair game play, then I will not support FunCom with my monthy fee.<br>
<br>
